      },
      {
        "location": "shipping-postal-network",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Shipping \\&amp; Postal Network",
        "text": "Field Value Variable Id iiag-infrastructure-shippostfac Definition Assesses the extent of a country's integration level into global shipping liner networks, using six components: i) the number of scheduled ships calls per week in the country; ii) deployed annual capacity in Twenty-Foot-equivalent Units (TEU): total deployed capacity offered at the country; iii) the number of regular liner shipping services from and to the country; iv) the number of liner shipping companies that provide services from and to the country; v) the average size in TEU of the ships deployed by the scheduled service with the largest average vessel size; vi) the number of the other countries that are connected to the country through direct liner shipping services. Format 0=Unknown or n.a.; 1=&lt;20%; 2=20-49%; 3=50-69%; 4=70-89%; 5=&gt;89% Other Metadata IIAG Series Id - ShipPostFac. Original data source/s - UNCTAD/UPU",
        "path": [],
        "tags": []
      },
      {
        "location": "public-perception-of-infrastructure",
        "level": 3,
        "title": "Public Perception of Infrastructure",
        "text": "Field Value Variable Id iiag-infrastructure-satinfr Definition Assesses the extent to which citizens feel the government is doing well at maintaining roads and bridges. Format 0=Unknown or n.a.; 1=&lt;20%; 2=20-49%; 3=50-69%; 4=70-89%; 5=&gt;89% Other Metadata IIAG Series Id - SatInfr. Original data source/s - AFR",
